  "text": "The Firefox codebase implements the Fetch API DOM interfaces defined in WebIDL files with corresponding C++ binding implementations. The mappings are as follows:\n\n1. **Request Interface**\n   - WebIDL Definition: dom/webidl/Request.webidl defines the Request interface per the WHATWG Fetch specification (https://fetch.spec.whatwg.org/#request-class)\n   - C++ Header Binding: dom/fetch/Request.h contains the Request class that extends FetchBody<Request> and nsWrapperCache\n   - C++ Implementation: dom/fetch/Request.cpp implements the Request interface methods\n   - The binding uses Request_Binding::Wrap to expose the interface to JavaScript\n\n2. **Response Interface**\n   - WebIDL Definition: dom/webidl/Response.webidl defines the Response interface per the WHATWG Fetch specification (https://fetch.spec.whatwg.org/#response-class)\n   - C++ Header Binding: dom/fetch/Response.h contains the Response class that extends FetchBody<Response> and nsWrapperCache\n   - C++ Implementation: dom/fetch/Response.cpp implements the Response interface methods\n   - The binding uses Response_Binding::Wrap to expose the interface to JavaScript\n\n3. **Headers Interface**\n   - WebIDL Definition: dom/webidl/Headers.webidl defines the Headers interface per the WHATWG Fetch specification (http://fetch.spec.whatwg.org/#headers-class)\n   - C++ Header Binding: dom/fetch/Headers.h contains the Headers class with backing by InternalHeaders\n   - C++ Implementation: dom/fetch/Headers.cpp implements the Headers interface methods including append, delete, get, has, set, and iteration\n   - The Headers class is only used for content-facing representation and is backed by InternalHeaders\n\n4. **FetchEvent Interface**\n   - WebIDL Definition: dom/webidl/FetchEvent.webidl defines the FetchEvent interface for Service Workers (per ServiceWorker spec)\n   - C++ Header Binding: dom/serviceworkers/ServiceWorkerEvents.h (line 132) contains the FetchEvent class that extends ExtendableEvent\n   - C++ Implementation: dom/serviceworkers/ServiceWorkerEvents.cpp implements the FetchEvent interface with respondWith method, request attribute, and preloadResponse, clientId, resultingClientId, and handled properties\n   - The binding uses FetchEventBinding to expose the interface to JavaScript\n\nAll WebIDL files are located in the dom/webidl/ directory. The C++ implementations for Request, Response, and Headers are co-located in dom/fetch/, while the FetchEvent implementation is in dom/serviceworkers/ because it is a Service Worker-specific event. The C++ classes properly implement their WebIDL interfaces using the Mozilla binding system with wrapper classes and property bindings."
}

